// Regression test: `import module.symbol as alias;` used to parse and pass
// semantic analysis but any call site using the alias failed at FLIR
// lowering with "call to unknown function <alias>" -- the alias was
// recorded on the IMPORT_STATEMENT node but nothing downstream ever
// consulted it. Fixed in imports.py's apply_symbol_aliases(), which
// rewrites alias call sites back to the imported symbol's original name
// right after each module (including the entry module) is parsed.
import @firescript/std.io.println as show;

show(5);

/* EXPECT
5
*/
